46) One-Line Recall Definitions for the Most Important Concepts
Here are quick memory lines:

Scope → Where a variable is accessible
Closure → A function remembering variables from outer scope
Hoisting → Declarations are processed before execution
this → Refers to the calling context of a function
Prototype → Object inheritance mechanism in JS
Promise → Object representing future async completion/failure
Async/await → Cleaner syntax for working with promises
Event loop → Mechanism that schedules async callbacks in JS
Destructuring → Extracting values from arrays/objects
Spread → Expanding iterable/object contents
Rest → Collecting multiple values into one
Module → File-level reusable code unit
Pure function → Same input, same output, no side effects
Mutability → Whether data can be changed
Shallow copy → Top-level copy only, nested refs still shared


